WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.920
Ripped Van Winkle and the legend of Sleepy Hollow by Washington Irving, copyright, black

00:15.920 --> 00:16.800
cat publishing.

00:30.160 --> 00:31.200
About the author.

00:32.320 --> 00:32.720
Name.

00:33.280 --> 00:36.400
Washington Irving, the father of American literature.

00:36.400 --> 00:37.200
Born.

00:37.200 --> 00:38.560
In New York City.

00:38.560 --> 00:38.880
When?

00:39.520 --> 00:41.520
April 3, 1783.

00:42.160 --> 00:42.800
First book.

00:43.440 --> 00:46.240
Knickerbacher's history of New York, 1809.

00:46.800 --> 00:47.840
Most famous stories.

00:48.640 --> 00:53.200
Ripped Van Winkle and the legend of Sleepy Hollow, 1819.

00:53.200 --> 00:53.760
Travels.

00:54.320 --> 00:57.600
England, Italy, Spain, France.

00:58.240 --> 00:58.720
Died.

00:59.200 --> 01:00.240
1859.

01:04.720 --> 01:06.960
Ripped Van Winkle, chapter one.

01:09.200 --> 01:10.560
The Van Winkle family.

01:11.280 --> 01:16.080
The Catskill Mountains are west of the Hudson River in the British colony of New York.

01:16.800 --> 01:20.560
The colors of these beautiful mountains change with the seasons.

01:21.120 --> 01:24.080
There are many legends and stories about them.

01:24.880 --> 01:27.280
The year is 1765.

01:27.680 --> 01:31.920
Ripped Van Winkle lives in a village at the foot of the Catskill Mountains.

01:31.920 --> 01:33.520
The village is of Dutch origin.

01:34.560 --> 01:37.680
Ripped lives an old, ugly house.

01:37.680 --> 01:39.520
He is a simple, kind man.

01:40.320 --> 01:43.920
Everyone in the village loves him because he is friendly and helpful.

01:44.640 --> 01:47.120
He plays with the children and makes things for them.

01:48.000 --> 01:50.480
Ripped's wife is very harsh with him.

01:50.480 --> 01:52.320
She nags him all the time.

01:52.880 --> 01:55.520
However, he is patient and obedient.

01:56.000 --> 01:57.920
He never gets angry at his wife.

01:57.920 --> 01:59.760
He simply keeps away from her.

02:00.960 --> 02:03.760
Ripped has only one bad point.

02:03.760 --> 02:05.680
He doesn't like working.

02:06.400 --> 02:08.080
He only does the things he likes.

02:09.040 --> 02:11.760
He sits on a rock and fishes all day.

02:12.400 --> 02:15.440
He walks in the forest and hunts animals.

02:15.440 --> 02:17.280
He builds fences for his friends.

02:17.840 --> 02:20.720
He helps the women in their homes and gardens.

02:20.800 --> 02:23.440
He does everyone's work, but not his own.

02:24.960 --> 02:27.440
His farm is the worst in the village.

02:27.440 --> 02:30.560
He never looks after his land, his garden, or his house.

02:31.200 --> 02:32.400
His fences are broken.

02:33.280 --> 02:35.440
His cow eats the vegetables in his garden.

02:36.080 --> 02:38.480
His children's clothes are old and dirty.

02:39.920 --> 02:42.720
Mrs. Van Winkle nags him about his laziness.

02:42.720 --> 02:44.240
Poor Ripped never says anything.

02:45.520 --> 02:47.280
He has a dog called Wolf.

02:48.160 --> 02:50.560
Mrs. Van Winkle doesn't like Wolf and Wolf.

02:50.720 --> 02:51.680
Doesn't like her.

02:52.400 --> 02:54.560
She often throws things at the poor animal.

02:56.240 --> 02:58.080
Ripped often goes to the village inn.

02:58.880 --> 03:02.320
It is called King George III in honor of the British king.

03:03.440 --> 03:06.080
There is a picture of King George outside the inn.

03:07.440 --> 03:10.720
The men of the village sit outside the inn during the summer.

03:10.720 --> 03:12.080
They talk and drink.

03:12.640 --> 03:15.840
They listen carefully to the school teacher, Derek Van Brummel.

03:16.560 --> 03:19.760
He is an educated man and uses long words.

03:21.440 --> 03:23.120
Nicholas Vetter is the innkeeper.

03:23.680 --> 03:26.400
He sits outside the inn from morning until night.

03:27.200 --> 03:29.920
Ripped likes going to the inn and talking to his friends.

03:29.920 --> 03:30.800
He's happy there.

03:31.600 --> 03:34.560
But Mrs. Van Winkle doesn't like the inn or his friends.

03:35.280 --> 03:38.240
This is a place for lazy men, she says.

03:38.880 --> 03:40.480
You must never go there again, Ripped.

03:45.920 --> 03:47.920
Page 16, exercise two.

03:48.880 --> 03:52.000
Listen to the following conversation twice.

03:52.000 --> 03:56.640
Then tick the correct answer, A, B, or C.

03:58.080 --> 03:59.680
Look at this house.

03:59.680 --> 04:01.280
All the fences are broken.

04:01.280 --> 04:02.480
You are right.

04:02.480 --> 04:04.480
You always build fences for Derek.

04:04.480 --> 04:06.480
He is my best friend.

04:06.480 --> 04:08.480
And I am your wife.

04:08.480 --> 04:10.880
I can build the fences on Tuesday.

04:10.880 --> 04:14.480
No, you must build the fences on Monday.

04:14.480 --> 04:16.960
But I must help my friend Nick.

04:16.960 --> 04:19.280
I must help my friend Nicholas on Monday.

04:19.280 --> 04:20.640
I don't like Nicholas.

04:20.640 --> 04:22.000
He's lazy.

04:22.000 --> 04:22.880
All right.

04:22.880 --> 04:25.200
I can build the fences on Monday.

04:25.200 --> 04:28.400
Then on Wednesday, you must work in the garden.

04:28.400 --> 04:29.760
Yes, of course.

04:29.760 --> 04:32.400
On Thursday, you must go to the market.

04:32.400 --> 04:33.840
What time is the market?

04:33.840 --> 04:36.320
It's at 9.30 a.m. and don't be late.

04:41.680 --> 04:45.200
Chapter 2, a strange afternoon.

04:46.000 --> 04:50.320
One autumn day, Ripped goes up the Catskill Mountains.

04:50.320 --> 04:54.080
After walking for many hours, he feels tired.

04:54.080 --> 04:59.040
He sits on a green hill and looks at the majestic Hudson River.

04:59.040 --> 05:02.000
And as he is looking at the sky, he says,

05:02.000 --> 05:03.760
It's almost evening.

05:03.760 --> 05:05.200
I must go home.

05:05.200 --> 05:08.160
My wife always gets angry when I'm late.

05:08.160 --> 05:11.680
As he's going down the mountain, he hears a voice.

05:11.680 --> 05:13.120
Ripped Van Winkle.

05:13.120 --> 05:14.880
Ripped Van Winkle.

05:14.960 --> 05:17.440
He looks around, but he sees no one.

05:17.440 --> 05:18.640
He hears someone call.

05:19.600 --> 05:20.560
Ripped Van Winkle.

05:21.360 --> 05:22.720
Ripped Van Winkle.

05:22.720 --> 05:23.680
Again.

05:23.680 --> 05:26.080
Then he sees a very strange man.

05:26.800 --> 05:29.520
He is climbing up the hill with something on his back.

05:30.240 --> 05:30.960
Ripped thinks,

05:31.600 --> 05:32.320
Who is this?

05:32.960 --> 05:34.240
No one ever comes here.

05:34.800 --> 05:35.920
Perhaps I can help him.

05:36.960 --> 05:40.560
Ripped walks towards the man and is very surprised.

05:40.560 --> 05:42.960
He sees a short, square old man.

05:43.680 --> 05:46.320
He has long, white hair and a beard.

05:46.960 --> 05:47.680
Ripped thinks,

05:48.240 --> 05:49.520
How bizarre.

05:49.520 --> 05:51.440
He's wearing very old clothes.

05:52.000 --> 05:54.800
They are Dutch clothes of the 1600s.

05:54.800 --> 05:55.840
Who is this man?

05:57.120 --> 06:00.320
The old man is carrying a small barrel on his back.

06:01.200 --> 06:03.600
Ripped helps the man and carries his barrel.

06:04.320 --> 06:06.080
Together they go up the valley.

06:06.960 --> 06:09.920
Ripped can hear the thunder, but he can't see the storm.

06:13.600 --> 06:16.480
Ripped follows the strange man.

06:16.480 --> 06:17.440
He thinks,

06:17.440 --> 06:19.840
Where are we going and why?

06:19.840 --> 06:23.200
Suddenly they walk into a small amphitheater.

06:23.200 --> 06:26.320
It is made of big stones and trees.

06:26.320 --> 06:28.880
There are some strange men there.

06:28.880 --> 06:32.560
They are all wearing Dutch clothes of the 1600s too.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.560
And they all have beards.

06:34.560 --> 06:36.160
There is a captain.

06:36.160 --> 06:38.160
He is wearing a captain's hat.

06:38.160 --> 06:41.120
He is a big, fat, round man.

06:41.120 --> 06:43.120
They are playing nine pins.

06:43.120 --> 06:45.440
The balls sound the same as thunder.

06:45.440 --> 06:47.440
No one is speaking.

06:47.440 --> 06:52.640
The mysterious silence and the cold eyes of the men scare Ripped.

06:52.640 --> 06:56.480
The old man points to the barrel and to the other old men.

06:56.480 --> 06:58.480
These men want to drink.

06:58.480 --> 06:59.440
Ripped thinks.

06:59.440 --> 07:02.960
He serves them and then they continue playing again.

07:02.960 --> 07:05.440
Ripped drinks from the barrel too.

07:05.440 --> 07:07.680
It is very strong.

07:07.680 --> 07:09.680
But Ripped likes it.

07:09.680 --> 07:11.680
He drinks again and again.

07:11.680 --> 07:15.680
Soon he falls asleep.

07:19.680 --> 07:21.680
Chapter 3.

07:21.680 --> 07:23.680
The next morning.

07:23.680 --> 07:27.680
Ripped wakes up the next morning and says,

07:27.680 --> 07:29.680
It's morning.

07:29.680 --> 07:31.680
Then he remembers the old man with the barrel.

07:31.680 --> 07:35.680
The game of nine pins and the old man with the barrel.

07:35.680 --> 07:39.680
The game of nine pins and the strong drink.

07:39.680 --> 07:41.680
My wife will be furious.

07:41.680 --> 07:43.680
What can I tell her?

07:43.680 --> 07:45.680
He looks for his gun and finds an old gun in its place.

07:45.680 --> 07:49.680
He calls his dog but the dog does not come.

07:49.680 --> 07:51.680
Those old men have my gun and my dog.

07:51.680 --> 07:53.680
I must find them.

07:53.680 --> 07:55.680
He gets up and tries to walk.

07:55.680 --> 07:57.680
It's difficult to walk.

07:57.680 --> 07:59.680
My poor legs.

07:59.680 --> 08:01.680
He thinks.

08:01.680 --> 08:03.680
He cannot find the old men or his dog.

08:03.680 --> 08:07.680
He is very hungry and decides to go home.

08:07.680 --> 08:11.680
He starts going down the mountain and when he is near the village he meets some people.

08:11.680 --> 08:13.680
How strange.

08:13.680 --> 08:17.680
I know everyone in the village but I don't know these people.

08:17.680 --> 08:19.680
Their clothes are very different.

08:19.680 --> 08:21.680
Thanks Ripped.

08:21.680 --> 08:23.680
The people look at him in his clothes.

08:23.680 --> 08:27.680
They are surprised and they touch their faces.

08:27.680 --> 08:29.680
Why are they touching their faces?

08:29.680 --> 08:31.680
Ripped thinks.

08:31.680 --> 08:33.680
He has his face and is surprised.

08:33.680 --> 08:37.680
He has a very long beard.

08:37.680 --> 08:45.680
When Ripped arrives at the village the children point at his grey beard and the dogs bark at him.

08:45.680 --> 08:51.680
The village looks different.

08:51.680 --> 08:53.680
It is very big.

08:53.680 --> 08:57.680
There are new houses with new names on the doors.

08:57.680 --> 08:59.680
He sees new faces everywhere.

08:59.680 --> 09:01.680
Everything is changed.

09:01.680 --> 09:04.680
Poor Ripped is very confused.

09:04.680 --> 09:06.680
How is this possible?

09:06.680 --> 09:08.680
This is my village.

09:08.680 --> 09:11.680
I can see the Catskill Mountains and the Hudson River.

09:11.680 --> 09:13.680
But everything is different.

09:13.680 --> 09:15.680
It must be the effect of the strong drink.

09:15.680 --> 09:17.680
Ripped thinks.

09:17.680 --> 09:19.680
He finds his house and goes in.

09:19.680 --> 09:21.680
It is abandoned.

09:21.680 --> 09:25.680
And all the windows are broken and there is no door.

09:25.680 --> 09:28.680
There is nothing in the house anymore.

09:28.680 --> 09:32.680
He calls for his wife and children but they don't answer him.

09:32.680 --> 09:35.680
What is happening? Where is my family?

09:35.680 --> 09:36.680
He thinks.

09:36.680 --> 09:38.680
He goes to the inn.

09:38.680 --> 09:41.680
He sees a big hotel in its place.

09:41.680 --> 09:43.680
Ripped reads the name on the door.

09:43.680 --> 09:45.680
The Union Hotel.

09:45.680 --> 09:48.680
Jonathan do little.

09:48.680 --> 09:52.680
He sees a tall pole in front of the hotel.

09:52.680 --> 09:54.680
On the pole there is a flag.

09:54.680 --> 09:57.680
There are stars and stripes on it.

09:57.680 --> 10:02.680
He goes inside the inn and looks for the picture of King George.

10:02.680 --> 10:04.680
He finds it but it is different.

10:04.680 --> 10:08.680
King George is wearing a blue coat instead of a red one

10:08.680 --> 10:11.680
and he is wearing a hat instead of a crown.

10:11.680 --> 10:16.680
Under the picture Ripped sees the words George Washington.

10:16.680 --> 10:22.680
Chapter 4.

10:22.680 --> 10:27.680
The Spirits of the Catskill Mountains.

10:27.680 --> 10:32.680
There are some people standing near the door of the Union Hotel.

10:32.680 --> 10:34.680
But Ripped does not know anyone.

10:34.680 --> 10:39.680
They are not quiet, slow and sleepy.

10:39.680 --> 10:42.680
They all seem noisy and fast.

10:42.680 --> 10:47.680
They talk quickly in loud voices.

10:47.680 --> 10:49.680
Where are my old friends?

10:49.680 --> 10:51.680
Ripped thinks.

10:51.680 --> 10:54.680
Ripped sees a thin man with many papers in his pockets.

10:54.680 --> 11:01.680
He is talking about political elections, liberty, the war of 76 and Congress.

11:01.680 --> 11:04.680
These new words confuse Ripped.

11:04.680 --> 11:06.680
What is this man saying?

11:06.680 --> 11:08.680
What is Congress?

11:08.680 --> 11:09.680
Is it a town?

11:09.680 --> 11:11.680
What war of 76?

11:11.680 --> 11:13.680
Ripped thinks.

11:13.680 --> 11:19.680
Soon everyone is looking at Ripped's long beard and strange clothes.

11:19.680 --> 11:21.680
The thin man asks him.

11:21.680 --> 11:24.680
Are you a federal or a Democrat?

11:24.680 --> 11:27.680
Ripped does not understand these words.

11:27.680 --> 11:29.680
An old gentleman asks Ripped.

11:29.680 --> 11:31.680
Why do you have a gun?

11:31.680 --> 11:33.680
Do you want to fight?

11:33.680 --> 11:35.680
Oh no, no.

11:35.680 --> 11:36.680
Says Ripped.

11:36.680 --> 11:40.680
I am a poor quiet man and King George is my king.

11:40.680 --> 11:42.680
What King George?

11:42.680 --> 11:44.680
The people cry.

11:44.680 --> 11:46.680
This man is a spy.

11:46.680 --> 11:48.680
He's not an American.

11:48.680 --> 11:49.680
Who is he?

11:49.680 --> 11:51.680
Call the police.

11:51.680 --> 11:53.680
The old gentleman asks.

11:53.680 --> 11:55.680
Why are you here?

11:55.680 --> 11:59.680
I'm looking for my friends, but I can't find them.

11:59.680 --> 12:00.680
Ripped says.

12:00.680 --> 12:02.680
Who are your friends?

12:02.680 --> 12:03.680
asks the old gentleman.

12:03.680 --> 12:05.680
Nicholas Vedder.

12:05.680 --> 12:06.680
Says Ripped.

12:06.680 --> 12:07.680
Nicholas Vedder.

12:07.680 --> 12:09.680
He's dead.

12:09.680 --> 12:11.680
And Brumm Dutcher.

12:11.680 --> 12:13.680
And Derek Brummel.

12:13.680 --> 12:15.680
Dutcher is dead.

12:15.680 --> 12:17.680
And Brummel is a congressman.

12:17.680 --> 12:19.680
Says the old gentleman.

12:19.680 --> 12:21.680
Ripped is unhappy and confused.

12:21.680 --> 12:25.680
I am alone in a strange world and no one knows me.

12:25.680 --> 12:27.680
Does anyone know Ripped Van Winkle?

12:27.680 --> 12:29.680
He cries.

12:29.680 --> 12:31.680
Oh Ripped Van Winkle.

12:31.680 --> 12:33.680
Cry to people.

12:33.680 --> 12:34.680
Yes.

12:34.680 --> 12:36.680
He's sitting under that tree.

12:36.680 --> 12:39.680
He looks and sees a young man with dirty old clothes.

12:39.680 --> 12:40.680
Is that me?

12:40.680 --> 12:42.680
Then who am I?

12:42.680 --> 12:44.680
asks Ripped.

12:44.680 --> 12:46.680
They look at him and say.

12:46.680 --> 12:48.680
He must be crazy.

12:48.680 --> 12:52.680
Then a young woman carefully looks at Ripped.

12:52.680 --> 12:53.680
Ripped asks.

12:53.680 --> 12:55.680
What is your name?

12:55.680 --> 12:57.680
Judith Gardner.

12:57.680 --> 12:59.680
What is your father's name?

12:59.680 --> 13:01.680
Ripped Van Winkle.

13:01.680 --> 13:05.680
Twenty years ago he went away and he never returned.

13:05.680 --> 13:06.680
She says.

13:06.680 --> 13:08.680
Where is your mother?

13:08.680 --> 13:10.680
Ripped asks.

13:10.680 --> 13:12.680
She is dead.

13:12.680 --> 13:15.680
Ripped embraces his daughter and says.

13:15.680 --> 13:16.680
I'm your father.

13:16.680 --> 13:18.680
I'm Ripped Van Winkle.

13:18.680 --> 13:20.680
I'm old now.

13:20.680 --> 13:22.680
He turns to the crowd and says.

13:22.680 --> 13:25.680
Does anyone remember Ripped Van Winkle?

13:25.680 --> 13:27.680
A very old woman says.

13:27.680 --> 13:28.680
Yes.

13:28.680 --> 13:31.680
This man is Ripped Van Winkle Sr.

13:31.680 --> 13:33.680
I remember him.

13:33.680 --> 13:36.680
Ripped tells his incredible story.

13:36.680 --> 13:41.680
The people of the village can't believe his story is true.

13:41.680 --> 13:44.680
They ask old Peter Vanderdonk.

13:44.680 --> 13:47.680
He is the oldest man in the village.

13:47.680 --> 13:52.680
He knows all the legends and stories of the Catskill Mountains.

13:52.680 --> 13:54.680
Peter Vanderdonk says.

13:54.680 --> 13:58.680
Mysterious things happen in the Catskill Mountains.

13:58.680 --> 14:00.680
There are strange spirits living there.

14:00.680 --> 14:05.680
People say that every twenty years Henry Hudson returns to see his river

14:05.680 --> 14:09.680
and that he and his men play nine pins in those mountains.

14:09.680 --> 14:13.680
It is late and the people of the village go home.

14:13.680 --> 14:16.680
Ripped goes to live with his daughter and her family

14:16.680 --> 14:19.680
and his son visits him every day.

14:19.680 --> 14:22.680
He is very similar to his father.

14:22.680 --> 14:25.680
He does everyone's work but not his own.

14:25.680 --> 14:27.680
Ripped makes some new friends.

14:27.680 --> 14:29.680
Everyone likes him.

14:29.680 --> 14:32.680
He doesn't really understand the American Revolutionary War

14:32.680 --> 14:36.680
or the new nation called the United States of America.

14:36.680 --> 14:38.680
But he is a happy man now.

14:38.680 --> 14:43.680
He sits outside the Union Hotel and tells stories about the past.

14:43.680 --> 14:48.680
He also tells travelers about his twenty year long sleep.

14:48.680 --> 14:51.680
Some people believe him, but some don't.

14:51.680 --> 14:59.680
Page 35, exercise two.

14:59.680 --> 15:06.680
After his long sleep, Ripped wants to know more about the United States.

15:06.680 --> 15:11.680
So he asks his friend, Congressman Derek Rummel.

15:11.680 --> 15:16.680
Listen to the interview between Ripped and Congressman Rummel.

15:16.680 --> 15:19.680
Then tick the correct answer.

15:19.680 --> 15:22.680
Are we still a British colony?

15:22.680 --> 15:25.680
No, we're not. We're free now.

15:25.680 --> 15:28.680
So we're not a colony anymore?

15:28.680 --> 15:31.680
No, we are a new nation.

15:31.680 --> 15:34.680
What is the name of this new nation?

15:34.680 --> 15:37.680
The United States of America.

15:37.680 --> 15:39.680
Who is our king?

15:39.680 --> 15:44.680
There isn't a king. We're a democracy now. We have a president.

15:44.680 --> 15:45.680
A president?

15:45.680 --> 15:50.680
Yes, a president. The people of the United States choose him.

15:50.680 --> 15:54.680
In a democracy, everyone is free and equal.

15:54.680 --> 15:57.680
The people choose their own government representatives.

15:57.680 --> 16:00.680
Really? Can I choose the president too?

16:00.680 --> 16:05.680
Yes, of course. At elections, you can vote for the president of the United States.

16:05.680 --> 16:07.680
Who is the president now?

16:07.680 --> 16:11.680
George Washington is our first president.

16:11.680 --> 16:19.680
George, but that's the same name as our king.

16:19.680 --> 16:23.680
Page 37, the American Revolution.

16:23.680 --> 16:25.680
Interview.

16:25.680 --> 16:31.680
A journalist from the Boston Gazette interviews General George Washington.

16:31.680 --> 16:37.680
Listen to the interview, then tick the correct answer.

16:37.680 --> 16:41.680
Hello, General Washington. What's happening in Boston?

16:41.680 --> 16:47.680
Well, there are 13 American colonies protesting against Great Britain, and I'm their leader.

16:47.680 --> 16:49.680
Why are you protesting?

16:49.680 --> 16:54.680
We don't want to obey British laws, and we don't want to pay taxes to King George.

16:54.680 --> 16:55.680
What do you want?

16:55.680 --> 16:59.680
We want to become an independent nation.

16:59.680 --> 17:01.680
What are you going to do?

17:01.680 --> 17:04.680
We are going to fight the British until we win.

17:04.680 --> 17:09.680
We have muskets, swords, horses, and many courageous men.

17:09.680 --> 17:14.680
We're called Yankees, but not all colonists are Yankees.

17:14.680 --> 17:17.680
Some are redcoats and fight with the British.

17:17.680 --> 17:20.680
What color are your uniforms?

17:20.680 --> 17:23.680
Our uniforms are blue and white.

17:23.680 --> 17:26.680
The British wear red jackets.

17:26.680 --> 17:32.680
On July 4th, my friends and I are going to sign the Declaration of Independence.

17:32.680 --> 17:34.680
What's that?

17:34.680 --> 17:40.680
It's a very important document that says the 13 colonies are free and independent states.

17:40.680 --> 17:42.680
Good luck to you and your men.

17:42.680 --> 17:44.680
Thank you.

17:44.680 --> 17:49.680
Today, Americans still celebrate July 4th, or Independence Day.

17:49.680 --> 17:51.680
It is a national holiday.

17:51.680 --> 17:59.680
The Legend of Sleepy Hollow.

17:59.680 --> 18:01.680
Chapter 1.

18:01.680 --> 18:04.680
The Headless Horseman.

18:04.680 --> 18:08.680
Greensburg is a village on the Hudson River.

18:08.680 --> 18:14.680
Near this village, there is a silent valley called Sleepy Hollow.

18:14.680 --> 18:17.680
It is the quietest place in the world.

18:17.680 --> 18:21.680
The inhabitants are always a bit sleepy there.

18:21.680 --> 18:26.680
Some people say there are bizarre spirits in this valley.

18:26.680 --> 18:30.680
Others say there are strange voices in the air.

18:30.680 --> 18:35.680
The people of Greensburg believe there is a ghost in Sleepy Hollow.

18:35.680 --> 18:40.680
It is the ghost of a headless man on a big horse.

18:40.680 --> 18:46.680
Legend says, it is the ghost of a soldier of the American Revolutionary War.

18:46.680 --> 18:50.680
His body is buried in the cemetery near the church.

18:50.680 --> 18:55.680
Every night he rides his horse and looks for his head.

18:55.680 --> 19:01.680
He rides in the valley near the river, in the forest and on the roads.

19:01.680 --> 19:05.680
He always returns to the cemetery before daylight.

19:05.680 --> 19:10.680
Everyone calls him the headless horseman of Sleepy Hollow.

19:10.680 --> 19:17.680
Chapter 2.

19:17.680 --> 19:20.680
Ichabod Crane.

19:20.680 --> 19:23.680
Ichabod Crane lives in Sleepy Hollow.

19:23.680 --> 19:28.680
He is a school teacher and comes from the state of Connecticut.

19:28.680 --> 19:31.680
He is tall and very thin.

19:31.680 --> 19:34.680
His legs and arms are very long.

19:34.680 --> 19:37.680
His feet are very big.

19:37.680 --> 19:43.680
His head is small with big ears, green eyes and a long nose.

19:43.680 --> 19:46.680
His clothes are always too big for him.

19:46.680 --> 19:51.680
Ichabod is always hungry and loves to eat.

19:51.680 --> 19:55.680
Ichabod is a good but strict teacher.

19:55.680 --> 19:58.680
His school is in the middle of the country.

19:58.680 --> 20:03.680
It has only one big room for all the pupils.

20:03.680 --> 20:09.680
After school, Ichabod plays ball with the older boys and on his free afternoons.

20:09.680 --> 20:12.680
He walks home with some of the younger ones.

20:12.680 --> 20:19.680
He always chooses the boys with pretty sisters, or generous mothers.

20:19.680 --> 20:25.680
Ichabod does not have much money, so every week he lives with a different family.

20:25.680 --> 20:30.680
He eats and sleeps at their house and keeps them company.

20:30.680 --> 20:37.680
When he changes family, he puts all his things in a big handkerchief and carries it with him.

20:37.680 --> 20:45.680
The farmers like him because he helps them with their work and the mothers like him because he plays with the small children.

20:45.680 --> 20:48.680
Ichabod also teaches singing.

20:48.680 --> 20:52.680
On Sundays he is the director of the church choir.

20:52.680 --> 20:54.680
He is very proud of this.

20:54.680 --> 20:59.680
The school teacher is an important person among farmers and their families.

20:59.680 --> 21:06.680
Everyone respects him because he is educated and the women consider him a gentleman.

21:06.680 --> 21:10.680
Ichabod likes gossiping and being the center of attention.

21:10.680 --> 21:15.680
He also likes eating all the good food the women prepare for him.

21:15.680 --> 21:18.680
Ichabod loves reading books.

21:18.680 --> 21:23.680
One of his favorite books is history of New England witchcraft.

21:23.680 --> 21:31.680
Ichabod believes the stories in this book. They are about ghosts and witches.

21:31.680 --> 21:35.680
During the winter Ichabod often visits the old women.

21:35.680 --> 21:45.680
They tell him terrible stories about ghosts, haunted houses, haunted trees, and the headless horsemen.

21:45.680 --> 21:52.680
When he returns home at night the sounds of the forest scare him.

21:53.680 --> 21:58.680
He thinks there are ghosts everywhere, so he sings church songs.

21:58.680 --> 22:04.680
A mighty fortress is our lord.

22:04.680 --> 22:07.680
Ichabod always sings these songs when he is afraid.

22:07.680 --> 22:12.680
Mmmmmm.

22:38.680 --> 22:42.680
Katrina's father has a big home with beautiful furniture.

22:42.680 --> 22:47.680
He also has a fine farm, many animals and lots of good food.

22:47.680 --> 22:54.680
Ichabod likes her father's riches. He also likes Katrina very much and wants to marry her.

22:54.680 --> 22:57.680
Oh, how I like Katrina.

22:57.680 --> 22:58.680
He thinks.

22:58.680 --> 23:01.680
How can I win her heart?

23:01.680 --> 23:06.680
Katrina has many admirers. They often visit the Vontassel house.

23:06.680 --> 23:10.680
Who does Katrina like? No one knows.

23:10.680 --> 23:15.680
One day she is nice to one young man, and the next day she is nice to another.

23:15.680 --> 23:22.680
Brom bones is the hero of sleepy hollow because he is tall, strong, and handsome.

23:22.680 --> 23:28.680
He has broad shoulders. He is a bit rough, but always cheerful.

23:28.680 --> 23:32.680
He is an excellent horseback rider and a courageous fighter.

23:32.680 --> 23:37.680
Everyone likes Brom, but sometimes he is mischievous and plays tricks.

23:37.680 --> 23:40.680
He is Ichabod's big rival.

23:40.680 --> 23:45.680
Brom often visits the Vontassel house and courts Katrina.

23:45.680 --> 23:53.680
When his horse is outside the Vontassel house, other admirers stay away.

23:53.680 --> 23:57.680
Ichabod also visits Katrina often because he is her singing teacher.

23:58.680 --> 24:03.680
He and Katrina sit together under the big tree singing and talking,

24:03.680 --> 24:06.680
or they walk together along the river in the evenings.

24:06.680 --> 24:11.680
Ichabod slowly wins Katrina's heart.

24:11.680 --> 24:16.680
Brom is very angry because he wants to marry beautiful Katrina.

24:16.680 --> 24:21.680
He decides to fight Ichabod, but Ichabod doesn't want to.

24:21.680 --> 24:25.680
Brom is big and strong. I cannot fight him and win.

24:25.680 --> 24:27.680
Ichabod thinks.

24:27.680 --> 24:30.680
Brom tries to make Ichabod angry.

24:30.680 --> 24:35.680
One night he goes into his school and he throws the tables and chairs about.

24:35.680 --> 24:39.680
The next day, Ichabod goes to school and says,

24:39.680 --> 24:42.680
Oh no, this is where the witches meet at night.

24:42.680 --> 24:48.680
Brom is very mischievous and teaches his dog to make terrible noises.

24:48.680 --> 24:50.680
Then he tells Katrina.

24:50.680 --> 24:55.680
Listen to my dog. His singing teacher is Ichabod Crane.

24:55.680 --> 25:00.680
But nothing can make Ichabod fight, so Brom is furious with him.

25:00.680 --> 25:02.680
I must find another way.

25:02.680 --> 25:04.680
Brom thinks.

25:08.680 --> 25:12.680
Page 57, exercise three.

25:12.680 --> 25:18.680
Listen to this dictation twice and fill in the missing words.

25:19.680 --> 25:22.680
Katrina is a beautiful girl.

25:22.680 --> 25:27.680
She lives in a lovely house on a big farm.

25:27.680 --> 25:33.680
Her father has a lot of animals and her mother prepares a lot of good food.

25:33.680 --> 25:38.680
She has many admirers and she is nice to all of them.

25:38.680 --> 25:43.680
Brom often visits Katrina because he likes her very much.

25:43.680 --> 25:46.680
He is a tall, handsome man.

25:47.680 --> 25:50.680
Ichabod is Katrina's singing teacher.

25:50.680 --> 25:53.680
He also visits Katrina often.

25:53.680 --> 25:59.680
Ichabod likes her father's farm and her mother's food a lot.

25:59.680 --> 26:02.680
He has very long arms and legs.

26:02.680 --> 26:05.680
He looks like a crane.

26:05.680 --> 26:08.680
Who does Katrina prefer?

26:09.680 --> 26:15.680
Page 58, New York in the 1800s.

26:15.680 --> 26:20.680
Mr. Fontassel writes a letter to his brother in Holland.

26:20.680 --> 26:26.680
Read the letter and learn about New York in the 1800s.

26:26.680 --> 26:30.680
Sleepy Hollow, October 28, 1820.

26:30.680 --> 26:37.680
Dear Peter, here I am in Sleepy Hollow in the state of New York.

26:37.680 --> 26:41.680
It is a very quiet place and it is full of farmers.

26:41.680 --> 26:43.680
My farm is very big.

26:43.680 --> 26:50.680
I have a lot of animals, vegetables and fruit trees but I must work very hard.

26:50.680 --> 26:54.680
Every week I go to the city of New York to sell my products.

26:54.680 --> 27:03.680
I sell apples, pears, pumpkins, vegetables, milk, butter, cheese and eggs.

27:03.680 --> 27:09.680
I put them all on a boat and then go down the Hudson River to New York City.

27:09.680 --> 27:13.680
The people there like good food from the country.

27:13.680 --> 27:18.680
Of course I take the food to a big market because New York City is really big.

27:18.680 --> 27:22.680
About 150,000 people live there.

27:22.680 --> 27:25.680
Everyone moves about very quickly.

27:25.680 --> 27:28.680
The streets are wide with many horse-drawn carriages.

27:28.680 --> 27:33.680
I like looking at the big shops and tall buildings especially in the business area.

27:33.680 --> 27:37.680
It is called Wall Street.

27:37.680 --> 27:41.680
New York has an important harbor with many factories near it.

27:41.680 --> 27:45.680
The ships in the harbor come from other American states or from Europe.

27:45.680 --> 27:52.680
I am always surprised by the big number of immigrants from Ireland, Germany and other countries.

27:52.680 --> 27:57.680
There are not many Indians on the streets but the ones you can see still wear their native dress.

27:58.680 --> 28:03.680
I hope you can come to visit me soon and see this cosmopolitan city.

28:03.680 --> 28:06.680
Your brother, Balthus.

28:12.680 --> 28:15.680
Chapter 4. The Invitation

28:15.680 --> 28:19.680
One autumn afternoon Ichabod is teaching at school.

28:19.680 --> 28:22.680
A messenger brings him a letter.

28:22.680 --> 28:26.680
It is an invitation to dinner at the Fontassel's house.

28:26.680 --> 28:29.680
Ichabod is happy and excited.

28:29.680 --> 28:34.680
His pupils are happy too because they finish school early.

28:34.680 --> 28:39.680
He puts on his best clothes, an old dark suit.

28:39.680 --> 28:42.680
Then he looks at himself in a broken mirror.

28:42.680 --> 28:44.680
I want to be handsome for Katrina.

28:44.680 --> 28:45.680
He thinks.

28:45.680 --> 28:48.680
This is an important occasion for me.

28:48.680 --> 28:52.680
Ichabod is staying at Van Ripper's farm this week.

28:52.680 --> 28:57.680
So after school, Ichabod returns to the farm and asks Van Ripper.

28:57.680 --> 29:00.680
Can I use your horse this evening?

29:00.680 --> 29:02.680
Yes, you can use gunpowder.

29:02.680 --> 29:08.680
He is old now and not very handsome. He has only one eye, but he is still a very good horse.

29:08.680 --> 29:10.680
Says Van Ripper.

29:10.680 --> 29:12.680
Thank you, Mr. Van Ripper.

29:12.680 --> 29:15.680
Says Ichabod. He looks at gunpowder and thinks.

29:15.680 --> 29:19.680
He is certainly an old horse, but he's better than nothing.

29:19.680 --> 29:24.680
Then he looks carefully into gunpowder's only eye and thinks.

29:24.680 --> 29:29.680
I see the devil in his eye. He is still a lively horse.

29:29.680 --> 29:32.680
Ichabod and gunpowder look funny together.

29:32.680 --> 29:37.680
Ichabod and his old suit and gunpowder with his one eye.

29:39.680 --> 29:45.680
They leave Van Ripper's farm, cross the forest, and ride along the Hudson River.

29:46.680 --> 29:49.680
Autumn is a beautiful season in Sleepy Hollow.

29:49.680 --> 29:57.680
There are many different colors, green, red, yellow, orange, purple, and brown.

29:57.680 --> 30:01.680
It is sunset and the sky is the color of gold.

30:01.680 --> 30:06.680
Along the road Ichabod sees orange pumpkins and apple trees.

30:06.680 --> 30:13.680
All he can think about are the delicious pies and cakes.

30:13.680 --> 30:16.680
Ichabod finally arrives at the Ventassel's house.

30:16.680 --> 30:19.680
All the farmers are there with their families.

30:19.680 --> 30:24.680
They are wearing their best clothes. Everyone is talking and laughing.

30:24.680 --> 30:26.680
It is a happy evening.

30:26.680 --> 30:28.680
Braum is there too.

30:28.680 --> 30:32.680
Everyone admires his horse, Daredevil.

30:32.680 --> 30:35.680
Daredevil is a big black horse.

30:35.680 --> 30:39.680
Only Braum can ride him because he is a dangerous animal.

30:39.680 --> 30:42.680
Braum is very proud of Daredevil.

30:43.680 --> 30:48.680
Ichabod is delighted when he sees the delicious food on the Ventassel's table.

30:48.680 --> 30:52.680
His big eyes move from one dish to the next.

30:52.680 --> 30:58.680
There are all kinds of cakes, sweet cakes, ginger cakes, and honey cakes.

30:58.680 --> 31:06.680
There are also pies, meat, fish, chicken, vegetables, fruit, and lots of milk.

31:06.680 --> 31:08.680
This is a royal banquet.

31:08.680 --> 31:09.680
He thinks?

31:09.680 --> 31:15.680
When I marry Katrina, I can have all this food, this beautiful home, and lots of money.

31:15.680 --> 31:20.680
I can laugh at Van Ripper and his old horse. I can laugh at everyone.

31:20.680 --> 31:23.680
Ichabod eats and drinks and is very happy.

31:23.680 --> 31:25.680
I'm very happy.

31:35.680 --> 31:39.680
Page 64, exercise two.

31:39.680 --> 31:42.680
What does Katrina write to Ichabod?

31:42.680 --> 31:46.680
Listen to the letter twice and fill in the gaps.

31:46.680 --> 31:51.680
Dear Ichabod, there is a Halloween party tonight.

31:51.680 --> 31:55.680
Please come to my house for dinner at 7.15 pm.

31:55.680 --> 32:00.680
I am making a chocolate cake. My mother is preparing a fruit cake.

32:00.680 --> 32:04.680
My grandmother is preparing a pumpkin pie.

32:04.680 --> 32:07.680
After dinner, we can walk in the garden.

32:07.680 --> 32:11.680
You can meet my five friends from New York.

32:11.680 --> 32:16.680
At 9.30 pm, we can dance and sing.

32:16.680 --> 32:19.680
Please wear your Halloween costume.

32:19.680 --> 32:21.680
Your friend, Katrina.

32:27.680 --> 32:32.680
Chapter 5, the ghost of Sleepy Hollow.

32:32.680 --> 32:36.680
After dinner, a small orchestra plays music.

32:36.680 --> 32:39.680
Ichabod dances with Katrina.

32:39.680 --> 32:41.680
He says sweet things to her.

32:41.680 --> 32:45.680
Katrina smiles at Ichabod and he smiles at her.

32:45.680 --> 32:49.680
Braum isn't dancing. He is sitting in a corner.

32:49.680 --> 32:54.680
He is watching Katrina and Ichabod. He is angry and jealous.

32:54.680 --> 32:58.680
Ichabod is a good dancer, but I can't dance.

32:58.680 --> 33:01.680
What can I do to win Katrina?

33:01.680 --> 33:05.680
After the dance, everyone goes outside and sits under the trees.

33:05.680 --> 33:09.680
They talk about the American Revolutionary War.

33:09.680 --> 33:14.680
When I look at the river, I remember the battles between the British and the Americans.

33:14.680 --> 33:17.680
I fought alone against the British with my small sword.

33:17.680 --> 33:19.680
Says an old farmer.

33:19.680 --> 33:21.680
A young farmer says.

33:21.680 --> 33:24.680
When the British saw my new musket, they ran away.

33:24.680 --> 33:27.680
We're all heroes of the American Revolutionary War.

33:27.680 --> 33:29.680
Says another man.

33:29.680 --> 33:32.680
They also talk about ghosts.

33:32.680 --> 33:34.680
Raven Rock is haunted.

33:34.680 --> 33:37.680
There's the ghost of a woman in white.

33:37.680 --> 33:40.680
I always see her ghost before a storm.

33:40.680 --> 33:42.680
She's scary.

33:42.680 --> 33:44.680
Says a young woman.

33:44.680 --> 33:48.680
When I pass by the big tree near the church, I hear terrible cries.

33:48.680 --> 33:50.680
It's the ghost of Major Andre.

33:50.680 --> 33:52.680
Says a boy.

33:52.680 --> 33:58.680
The headless horseman is the most horrible. He gallops on his big black horse and follows you.

33:58.680 --> 34:00.680
Sometimes he takes you away.

34:00.680 --> 34:03.680
When there is a full moon, you can see him clearly.

34:03.680 --> 34:05.680
Says a tall man.

34:05.680 --> 34:09.680
Ichabod listens to these stories and believes them.

34:10.680 --> 34:14.680
Soon the farmers and their families start going home.

34:14.680 --> 34:18.680
Ichabod wants to stay and talk to Katrina.

34:18.680 --> 34:22.680
This is the right moment. I must ask Katrina to marry me.

34:22.680 --> 34:24.680
He thinks.

34:24.680 --> 34:27.680
No one knows what happens between Katrina and Ichabod,

34:27.680 --> 34:31.680
but he is very sad when he leaves the Fantasal house.

34:31.680 --> 34:33.680
Does Katrina prefer brom?

34:34.680 --> 34:38.680
Ichabod gets on gunpowder and starts riding to Van Ripper's farm.

34:38.680 --> 34:41.680
It is a very dark night.

34:41.680 --> 34:43.680
Clouds cover the stars.

34:43.680 --> 34:47.680
Ichabod thinks about the ghosts of sleepy hollow.

34:47.680 --> 34:51.680
He hears a strange noise in the forest.

34:51.680 --> 34:53.680
Is it the voice of a ghost?

34:53.680 --> 34:55.680
Or is the wind?

34:55.680 --> 34:58.680
Something is moving in the sky.

34:58.680 --> 35:00.680
Is it a witch?

35:00.680 --> 35:04.680
Is it the ghost of the woman in white?

35:04.680 --> 35:06.680
What a mysterious night.

35:06.680 --> 35:08.680
Ichabod thinks.

35:08.680 --> 35:10.680
He is lonely and sad.

35:10.680 --> 35:14.680
He rides very quickly.

35:14.680 --> 35:18.680
He comes to a brook with a small bridge.

35:18.680 --> 35:21.680
It is very difficult to cross the bridge.

35:21.680 --> 35:25.680
On the other side of the brook, Ichabod sees some enormous trees.

35:25.680 --> 35:29.680
It is dark and he is afraid.

35:30.680 --> 35:33.680
Major Andrei's ghost lives here.

35:33.680 --> 35:34.680
He thinks.

35:34.680 --> 35:37.680
I must cross this bridge quickly.

35:37.680 --> 35:39.680
Ichabod kicks gunpowder and says,

35:39.680 --> 35:42.680
Come on gunpowder, cross the bridge quickly.

35:42.680 --> 35:45.680
But the old horse does not move.

35:45.680 --> 35:49.680
Ichabod kicks gunpowder again and again.

35:49.680 --> 35:53.680
Finally the horse moves, but then he stops suddenly.

35:53.680 --> 35:56.680
Ichabod nearly falls off.

35:56.680 --> 35:59.680
He is very nervous.

35:59.680 --> 36:01.680
What is happening to me tonight?

36:01.680 --> 36:02.680
He thinks.

36:02.680 --> 36:06.680
Then he hears a strange sound on the other side of the brook.

36:06.680 --> 36:11.680
In the shadow of the trees, he sees something big and black.

36:13.680 --> 36:16.680
Oh no, something is waiting for me.

36:16.680 --> 36:18.680
It isn't moving.

36:18.680 --> 36:20.680
It is waiting for me.

36:20.680 --> 36:22.680
I cannot go back.

36:22.680 --> 36:24.680
What must I do?

36:25.680 --> 36:27.680
His heart is beating fast.

36:27.680 --> 36:29.680
His hair is standing up.

36:29.680 --> 36:33.680
His mouth is dry and his hands are very cold.

36:33.680 --> 36:35.680
Who are you?

36:35.680 --> 36:37.680
Ichabod asks.

36:37.680 --> 36:39.680
There is no answer.

36:39.680 --> 36:41.680
Who are you?

36:41.680 --> 36:43.680
He asks again.

36:43.680 --> 36:45.680
His teeth are chattering.

36:45.680 --> 36:48.680
There is still no answer.

36:48.680 --> 36:53.680
Ichabod closes his eyes and starts singing a church song.

36:54.680 --> 36:58.680
At that moment, the big black thing moves again.

36:58.680 --> 37:02.680
It jumps out into the road and Ichabod opens his eyes.

37:02.680 --> 37:08.680
The night is dark, but he can see a horseman on a big black horse.

37:13.680 --> 37:16.680
Chapter 6, the night ride.

37:17.680 --> 37:20.680
Ichabod forces the horse to gallop.

37:20.680 --> 37:22.680
The horseman follows him.

37:22.680 --> 37:26.680
Ichabod thinks about the horrible stories of the headless horseman.

37:26.680 --> 37:31.680
Gunpowder gallops fast, but the horseman gallops fast too.

37:31.680 --> 37:35.680
Ichabod wants to sing a church song, but his mouth is dry.

37:35.680 --> 37:37.680
They gallop up a hill.

37:37.680 --> 37:41.680
Against the night sky, Ichabod sees the horseman.

37:41.680 --> 37:43.680
He is headless.

37:43.680 --> 37:46.680
He is carrying his head on his saddle.

37:46.680 --> 37:48.680
Ichabod is terrified.

37:48.680 --> 37:50.680
He hits gunpowder again and again.

37:50.680 --> 37:53.680
He wants the old horse to gallop fast.

37:53.680 --> 37:58.680
But the headless horseman follows him with his big black horse.

37:58.680 --> 38:03.680
The road to Van Ripper's farm is on the left, but gunpowder turns right.

38:03.680 --> 38:07.680
This road goes to the church bridge and the church cemetery.

38:07.680 --> 38:10.680
Ichabod and gunpowder gallop down the hill.

38:10.680 --> 38:15.680
Suddenly, Ichabod's saddle falls off, but the horse does not stop.

38:15.680 --> 38:16.680
Oh no.

38:16.680 --> 38:18.680
Think, Ichabod?

38:18.680 --> 38:21.680
That is Van Ripper's best saddle.

38:21.680 --> 38:24.680
Ichabod clasps gunpowder's neck.

38:24.680 --> 38:26.680
He tries to stay on the horse.

38:26.680 --> 38:29.680
The headless horseman is behind him.

38:29.680 --> 38:31.680
Ichabod is very scared.

38:31.680 --> 38:33.680
His teeth are chattering.

38:33.680 --> 38:35.680
The church bridge is near here.

38:35.680 --> 38:37.680
He thinks.

38:37.680 --> 38:40.680
Ghosts usually disappear after the church bridge.

38:40.680 --> 38:42.680
I must cross the bridge.

38:42.680 --> 38:44.680
Then I'm safe.

38:44.680 --> 38:47.680
Ichabod and gunpowder gallop across the church bridge.

38:47.680 --> 38:51.680
Ichabod looks back, and the headless horseman is still there.

38:51.680 --> 38:54.680
He has a big round object in his hands.

38:54.680 --> 38:57.680
He throws it at Ichabod.

38:57.680 --> 38:59.680
It's his head!

38:59.680 --> 39:00.680
Crys Ichabod.

39:00.680 --> 39:04.680
The big head hits Ichabod, and there is a loud thud.

39:04.680 --> 39:08.680
Ichabod falls to the ground and gunpowder gallops away.

39:08.680 --> 39:12.680
The next morning, gunpowder arrives at Van Ripper's farm,

39:12.680 --> 39:15.680
but Ichabod isn't there for breakfast.

39:15.680 --> 39:17.680
Ichabod isn't at school.

39:17.680 --> 39:20.680
And he isn't there for breakfast.

39:20.680 --> 39:22.680
Ichabod isn't there for breakfast.

39:22.680 --> 39:25.680
Ichabod isn't there for breakfast.

39:25.680 --> 39:27.680
Ichabod isn't at school.

39:27.680 --> 39:30.680
And he isn't at Van Ripper's farm.

39:30.680 --> 39:32.680
Where is Ichabod?

39:32.680 --> 39:33.680
Ask Van Ripper.

39:33.680 --> 39:35.680
And where is my best saddle?

39:35.680 --> 39:39.680
Van Ripper and his friends look for Ichabod everywhere.

39:39.680 --> 39:42.680
They find the saddle on the road near the church.

39:42.680 --> 39:46.680
They find Ichabod's hat and a broken pumpkin near the river.

39:46.680 --> 39:49.680
But they can't find Ichabod's body.

39:49.680 --> 39:51.680
Ichabod is a headless horseman.

39:51.680 --> 39:53.680
Poor Ichabod Crane.

39:53.680 --> 39:55.680
Says Van Ripper.

39:55.680 --> 39:57.680
Yes, it's the headless horseman.

39:57.680 --> 39:59.680
Oh, poor Ichabod!

39:59.680 --> 40:01.680
Say his friends.

40:01.680 --> 40:07.680
Years later, an old farmer returning from New York says to the people of Sleepy Hollow.

40:07.680 --> 40:09.680
Ichabod Crane is alive and well.

40:09.680 --> 40:11.680
Now he is a congressman.

40:11.680 --> 40:16.680
He left Sleepy Hollow because Katrina wanted to marry brom bones.

40:16.680 --> 40:19.680
Hearing this asks her husband brom.

40:19.680 --> 40:23.680
What do you know about Ichabod Crane in the pumpkin?

40:23.680 --> 40:26.680
Brom laughs loudly.

40:26.680 --> 40:36.680
At Sleepy Hollow, people say that only brom knows the true story of Ichabod Crane and the headless horseman.

40:36.680 --> 40:39.680
It is brom's secret.

40:39.680 --> 40:45.680
Now, on winter evenings, the old women tell the terrible story of Ichabod Crane

40:45.680 --> 40:47.680
and the headless horseman.

